    "body": "> I have encountered a similar problem once when running `brew upgrade` and another time when running `albemic revision --autogenerate`. Looks like any subprocess that is able to run for a noticeably long period of time might be able to trigger this.\n> \n> The time taken is also very curiously `1m25s` ~every time~ (update: not exactly every time) which was clearly not true.\n> \n> OTOH if there's nothing to be upgraded, `brew upgrade` will terminate normally in a few seconds and the prompt works as usual.\n> \n> If it helps, I'm using macOS 26.1.\n\nUpdate: It looks like the `unknown -f` and the timer being stuck are two separate issues. I'll report this to #7185 as well.",
